import React, { useState } from "react"
import { BrowserRouter as Router, Route, Switch } from "react-router-dom"

import Splash from "/home/ubuntu/dev/src/pages/splash/Splash.js"
import Access from "/home/ubuntu/dev/src/pages/access/js/Access.js"
import Frontpage from "/home/ubuntu/dev/src/pages/frontpage/js/Frontpage.js"

import AuthContext from "./AuthContext.js"

export default function CustomRoutes() {

  const [authenticated, setAuthenticated] = useState(false);
  
  return (
    <AuthContext.Provider value={{ authenticated, setAuthenticated }}>
      <Router>
        <Switch>
          <Route exact path="/">
            {
              authenticated ?
                <Frontpage /> :
                <Splash />
            }
          </Route>

          <Route path="/frontpage" >
            {
              authenticated ?
                <Frontpage /> :
                <Splash />
            }
          </Route>

          <Route path="/access" >
            {
              authenticated ?
                <Redirect to="/frontpage" /> :
                <Access />
            }
          </Route>
        </Switch>
      </Router>
    </AuthContext.Provider>
  )
}
